1
00:00:00,300 --> 00:00:02,533
you just couldn't resist, could you?

2
00:00:03,000 --> 00:00:05,466
the allure of magic was far too strong

3
00:00:06,033 --> 00:00:08,633
mastering gregtech power isn't enough for you

4
00:00:09,200 --> 00:00:11,866
only absolute power will suffice

5
00:00:11,866 --> 00:00:13,233
magical infusion

6
00:00:13,500 --> 00:00:15,300
bloody sacrifice

7
00:00:15,800 --> 00:00:17,266
a witchery brew

8
00:00:17,933 --> 00:00:20,533
you want it all, you need it all

9
00:00:21,333 --> 00:00:22,533
but where does it begin

10
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:25,433
right here of course

11
00:00:25,500 --> 00:00:26,666
congratulations

12
00:00:26,833 --> 00:00:29,600
the Hogwarts letter you've been waiting for all your life has just arrived

13
00:00:29,933 --> 00:00:32,866
welcome to the beginners guide to gregtech new horizons

14
00:00:33,066 --> 00:00:36,133
this is episode six, magic

15
00:00:49,866 --> 00:00:51,166
here we are in the new base

16
00:00:51,166 --> 00:00:52,433
recognize the design?

17
00:00:53,200 --> 00:00:56,966
today we cover the basics of Thaumcraft, Botania, witchery and blood magic

18
00:00:57,533 --> 00:01:01,333
enough to get you going and on your way towards the many delights magic can offer you in GTNH

19
00:01:02,066 --> 00:01:04,000
oh right this is GTNH

20
00:01:04,500 --> 00:01:08,566
which means magic is way more useful and well integrated than anything you've ever seen

21
00:01:08,566 --> 00:01:10,833
and also a bit more complicated than usual

22
00:01:12,466 --> 00:01:14,333
as always, first things first

23
00:01:14,700 --> 00:01:17,400
keep in mind that all this is optional at least for now

24
00:01:17,400 --> 00:01:18,733
but has huge benefits

25
00:01:19,433 --> 00:01:21,266
and like everything else, the earlier you get them

26
00:01:21,266 --> 00:01:22,466
the more payoff they have

27
00:01:22,900 --> 00:01:25,933
it's still a bit early in overall progression to go too nuts with magic

28
00:01:26,033 --> 00:01:27,300
but now that you have aluminum

29
00:01:27,466 --> 00:01:31,033
and a while to wait to get enough stuff to make the power system you planned after last episode

30
00:01:31,033 --> 00:01:31,933
you can get started

31
00:01:32,300 --> 00:01:33,800
and if you've gotten a bit lucky with loot

32
00:01:33,833 --> 00:01:35,000
you can take it pretty far

33
00:01:35,266 --> 00:01:37,966
the long and short is you need stainless steel

34
00:01:37,966 --> 00:01:40,600
16 ingots in total to take you through everything you're gonna see here

35
00:01:40,600 --> 00:01:41,700
and a couple of eyes of ender

36
00:01:41,700 --> 00:01:44,933
which you can get from villagers before you have machines that can make them in hv

37
00:01:45,433 --> 00:01:46,700
even if you did get lucky with loot

38
00:01:46,700 --> 00:01:48,800
this guide will take you until the end of MV to complete

39
00:01:48,800 --> 00:01:50,233
and you'll need some MV machines

40
00:01:50,233 --> 00:01:51,133
so keep that in mind

41
00:01:51,433 --> 00:01:52,600
and that's far from all you need

42
00:01:52,600 --> 00:01:55,700
you certainly won't be finishing magic progression with just that

43
00:01:55,866 --> 00:01:57,100
but this is the beginner's guide

44
00:01:57,133 --> 00:01:58,033
so let's begin

45
00:02:01,233 --> 00:02:02,500
it all starts with thaumcraft

46
00:02:03,000 --> 00:02:06,400
it's no coincidence that this is the first magic mod the quest book calls out

47
00:02:06,400 --> 00:02:08,200
to get started on any of the other magic mods

48
00:02:08,200 --> 00:02:09,866
you'll need to make some progress with thaumcraft

49
00:02:10,466 --> 00:02:12,900
it might appear that getting aluminum will unlock the quest chapter

50
00:02:12,900 --> 00:02:14,600
but if you didn't unlock it when you went to the twilight

51
00:02:14,600 --> 00:02:18,033
what you actually need is a quest way back in the "so it begins" chapter

52
00:02:18,600 --> 00:02:19,400
what's that

53
00:02:20,533 --> 00:02:22,433
if you can't find silverwood or greatwood trees

54
00:02:22,433 --> 00:02:23,933
buy the saplings from the quest book

55
00:02:24,266 --> 00:02:25,633
if you haven't been doing the side quests

56
00:02:25,633 --> 00:02:28,100
you might have to do a few now to get the right coins

57
00:02:28,100 --> 00:02:30,233
either way, you can start thinking about your first wand

58
00:02:30,766 --> 00:02:32,500
you've been to the twilight to do some mining

59
00:02:32,500 --> 00:02:34,566
now it's time to go back and do some fighting

60
00:02:34,566 --> 00:02:37,200
oh, and more mining

61
00:02:37,433 --> 00:02:38,333
before you go boss hunting

62
00:02:38,333 --> 00:02:39,500
you might want to pause for a bit

63
00:02:39,500 --> 00:02:41,833
and check out the introductory quests in the thaumcraft chapter

64
00:02:42,600 --> 00:02:46,333
firstly, ironwood is handy if you didn't grind out the cobalt pickaxe head already

65
00:02:46,633 --> 00:02:48,666
and the armor is pretty good too, at least for now

66
00:02:49,333 --> 00:02:51,233
the magic map is also worth grabbing now

67
00:02:51,233 --> 00:02:54,100
since it'll point you directly to the bosses you need to slay

68
00:02:54,100 --> 00:02:56,866
speaking of, there are lots of them

69
00:02:56,866 --> 00:02:57,833
but for early progression

70
00:02:57,833 --> 00:02:59,200
you only need to kill two

71
00:02:59,200 --> 00:03:00,900
the Naga and the Lich king

72
00:03:01,733 --> 00:03:02,966
the Naga isn't super dangerous

73
00:03:02,966 --> 00:03:04,200
if you have a few extra hearts

74
00:03:04,200 --> 00:03:05,333
you can probably run right at them

75
00:03:05,333 --> 00:03:06,633
and start swinging with a decent sword

76
00:03:06,633 --> 00:03:08,333
or shooting with your carbon limb crossbow

77
00:03:09,000 --> 00:03:10,166
and if you have it in you

78
00:03:10,166 --> 00:03:10,633
kill a few

79
00:03:10,633 --> 00:03:12,833
to make the first wand, you only need two scales

80
00:03:12,833 --> 00:03:16,033
but you'll need to craft an upgrade before you can make a wand that uses the next boss drop

81
00:03:18,600 --> 00:03:19,833
if you want to stop after the Naga

82
00:03:19,833 --> 00:03:20,833
and do the next part later

83
00:03:20,833 --> 00:03:21,233
feel free

84
00:03:21,233 --> 00:03:23,333
but the Lich is only slightly more complicated

85
00:03:23,900 --> 00:03:25,000
pillar up to the boss room

86
00:03:25,000 --> 00:03:26,533
it should be pretty obvious which one it is

87
00:03:26,533 --> 00:03:27,500
and break straight in

88
00:03:28,000 --> 00:03:29,066
while the boss is waking up

89
00:03:29,066 --> 00:03:32,066
block off the staircase so the mobs below don't wander into the Arena

90
00:03:32,233 --> 00:03:35,266
a creeper explosion at this moment would be most untimely

91
00:03:36,366 --> 00:03:37,800
draw your sword and start swinging

92
00:03:37,800 --> 00:03:39,100
this time to keep the zombies at Bay

93
00:03:39,100 --> 00:03:42,633
and try to reflect the flying interpoles (?) back at the boss to remove the shields that are circling them

94
00:03:42,933 --> 00:03:45,066
once they're gone, slay on slayer

95
00:03:45,633 --> 00:03:46,266
if you get pinched

96
00:03:46,266 --> 00:03:48,633
hide in one of the side rooms or just bail out of the room

97
00:03:48,800 --> 00:03:52,733
a few red hearts can be handy for instant regen if you've gotten any from your blaze farm

98
00:03:52,733 --> 00:03:54,500
again, a couple of boss kills can be worth it

99
00:03:54,666 --> 00:03:56,533
but by the time you're using Lich bones to make wands

100
00:03:56,533 --> 00:03:59,466
you'll be ready to make a bit of salas mudus to craft the bones using the trophy

101
00:04:01,033 --> 00:04:02,133
before you leave the twilight

102
00:04:02,133 --> 00:04:04,000
grab a couple stacks worth of every shard ore

103
00:04:04,433 --> 00:04:06,500
ore doubling these is painfully slow

104
00:04:06,500 --> 00:04:08,466
so you might want to start by smelting them directly

105
00:04:09,100 --> 00:04:12,466
if so, consider grabbing the silky jewel reward from the twilight forest quest

106
00:04:12,466 --> 00:04:13,866
either way get plenty

107
00:04:14,600 --> 00:04:15,466
and once you're home

108
00:04:15,466 --> 00:04:17,566
crafting the wand is elementary

109
00:04:17,566 --> 00:04:18,733
ollendor delights (?)

110
00:04:21,133 --> 00:04:22,866
now the snowball can start rolling

111
00:04:22,866 --> 00:04:26,133
right click a bookshelf with the wand to get your thaumonicon

112
00:04:26,133 --> 00:04:29,066
right click a table with the wand to get your arcane worktable

113
00:04:32,700 --> 00:04:35,100
right click a cauldron with the wand to get your crucible

114
00:04:37,666 --> 00:04:40,900
right click two tables with describing tools to get your research station

115
00:04:44,200 --> 00:04:46,300
and then use your shards to make the thaumometer

116
00:04:46,933 --> 00:04:49,800
you've acquired the basics your trip to hogsmeade (?) has concluded

117
00:04:52,633 --> 00:04:54,700
and just like that the Hogwarts express has dropped you off

118
00:04:54,700 --> 00:04:55,833
and you're in your first lesson

119
00:04:55,866 --> 00:04:57,100
so pay close attention

120
00:04:57,700 --> 00:05:01,233
thaumcraft research is a minigame that spends points to complete a chain of aspects

121
00:05:01,500 --> 00:05:04,666
aspects are the core elements of magic that everything in the game is composed of

122
00:05:05,433 --> 00:05:07,000
everything is made up of different aspects

123
00:05:07,000 --> 00:05:09,733
and every research is made up of different sequences of aspects

124
00:05:09,733 --> 00:05:13,033
that need to be connected via other aspects that share part of their makeup

125
00:05:13,033 --> 00:05:14,733
before we worry too much about that

126
00:05:14,733 --> 00:05:16,466
you need to accumulate some aspects

127
00:05:16,900 --> 00:05:19,700
the quest book has a nice list of what to scan for all the aspects soon

128
00:05:19,700 --> 00:05:21,466
don't worry too much about what you've unlocked

129
00:05:21,466 --> 00:05:22,833
just scan the list of things for now

130
00:05:24,933 --> 00:05:26,800
you can either hold the thaumometer and look at things

131
00:05:26,800 --> 00:05:28,600
or hover over items in your inventory

132
00:05:29,133 --> 00:05:32,400
as the quest book indicates, the first set of things needs to be scanned in order

133
00:05:32,466 --> 00:05:33,466
don't skip any

134
00:05:33,466 --> 00:05:35,866
scan as many of the other things in the list as you have or can find

135
00:05:35,866 --> 00:05:37,433
and be prepared to make things

136
00:05:37,433 --> 00:05:38,700
or go kill mobs for loot

137
00:05:38,700 --> 00:05:39,433
or go hunting

138
00:05:39,900 --> 00:05:42,400
if you get a message that you're missing knowledge to scan an item

139
00:05:42,400 --> 00:05:44,733
skip it, and circle back to it next time you see that message

140
00:05:45,266 --> 00:05:48,400
this is a one time effort to unlock knowledge of all the aspects

141
00:05:48,400 --> 00:05:50,100
so knuckle down and get it done

142
00:05:50,100 --> 00:05:51,933
for the tainted anything item

143
00:05:52,066 --> 00:05:54,033
your best bet is finding a tainted lands biome

144
00:05:54,700 --> 00:05:56,666
you might be traveling quite a while to find one

145
00:05:56,666 --> 00:05:57,533
use the biome compass

146
00:05:57,600 --> 00:06:00,566
and find a magical forest while you're out if you haven't already

147
00:06:00,566 --> 00:06:01,866
once you find the tainted lands

148
00:06:01,866 --> 00:06:03,433
scan something tainted then bail

149
00:06:03,433 --> 00:06:05,233
and do not chunkload this area

150
00:06:05,233 --> 00:06:07,266
if you base near it, move

151
00:06:07,266 --> 00:06:09,400
no matter how time consuming it'll be

152
00:06:10,000 --> 00:06:14,066
you have just observed the future of your base and the entire world if you aren't careful

153
00:06:14,300 --> 00:06:15,400
all consumed in tainted

154
00:06:15,833 --> 00:06:18,766
which is why i don't recommend experimenting with the method the quest book recommends

155
00:06:18,766 --> 00:06:20,600
unless you have some experience

156
00:06:21,100 --> 00:06:22,700
now that you have all the aspects

157
00:06:22,700 --> 00:06:24,800
scan literally everything you own

158
00:06:26,800 --> 00:06:29,700
you can review them in NEI to see which items produce those aspects when scanned

159
00:06:29,700 --> 00:06:31,333
or run through the alchemical furnace

160
00:06:33,600 --> 00:06:35,800
take another look at your research station now too

161
00:06:35,800 --> 00:06:36,866
all the aspects are there

162
00:06:36,866 --> 00:06:38,733
ready to be used for the research minigame

163
00:06:39,100 --> 00:06:42,566
each has a number representing how many points worth that aspect you have scanned

164
00:06:42,566 --> 00:06:43,666
to accumulate more

165
00:06:43,666 --> 00:06:46,133
you need to scan new items that contain that aspect type

166
00:06:46,633 --> 00:06:50,100
in general you'll want to scan basically every new thing you encounter in craft going forward

167
00:06:50,100 --> 00:06:52,433
and go back and scan every single thing you possess

168
00:06:53,066 --> 00:06:57,400
you'll probably notice that you accumulate more of a couple particular aspects than you do anything else

169
00:06:57,400 --> 00:06:59,700
due to how many unique machines you have laying around to scan

170
00:07:00,233 --> 00:07:01,700
ordo and instrumentum

171
00:07:04,200 --> 00:07:06,000
if benzene is the metaphor for power

172
00:07:06,133 --> 00:07:08,666
ordo and instrumentum are the metaphor for thaumcraft research

173
00:07:09,400 --> 00:07:10,866
aside from the primal aspects

174
00:07:10,866 --> 00:07:14,066
every other aspect is made up from two other aspects

175
00:07:14,833 --> 00:07:17,666
for example, air plus ordo makes motus

176
00:07:19,300 --> 00:07:21,233
with scribe tools and paper in your inventory

177
00:07:21,233 --> 00:07:24,000
click on none research in the thaumonicon to get a research sheet

178
00:07:24,000 --> 00:07:26,600
and stick it in the table with the scribe tools

179
00:07:27,033 --> 00:07:32,600
the way the research minigame works is by connecting the aspects that start on the research sheet using other aspects that are made up from them

180
00:07:33,600 --> 00:07:35,300
motus can be placed beside ordo

181
00:07:35,300 --> 00:07:37,500
because motus is composed of ordo

182
00:07:37,500 --> 00:07:39,300
air can be placed on the other side of motus

183
00:07:39,300 --> 00:07:41,666
because motus is also composed of air

184
00:07:41,666 --> 00:07:44,833
now we have a link between ordo and air via motus

185
00:07:46,500 --> 00:07:47,533
to complete the research

186
00:07:47,533 --> 00:07:50,033
you simply connect all the aspects using the same idea

187
00:07:50,066 --> 00:07:52,633
both different aspects depending on what the research starts with

188
00:07:52,666 --> 00:07:53,233
make sense?

189
00:07:53,233 --> 00:07:54,900
after you play with it for a bit

190
00:07:54,900 --> 00:07:59,900
you may notice that almost every research can be completed by first converting the starting aspects into ordo or instrumentum

191
00:07:59,900 --> 00:08:02,200
and then alternating between the two to bridge gaps

192
00:08:02,666 --> 00:08:04,566
things should be loaded with both of these things

193
00:08:04,566 --> 00:08:06,700
and might struggle to get anything else in large supply

194
00:08:06,833 --> 00:08:07,733
this is the way

195
00:08:09,233 --> 00:08:10,333
as you unlock research

196
00:08:10,333 --> 00:08:13,000
you'll notice that some of them are labeled forbidden knowledge

197
00:08:13,000 --> 00:08:15,066
with varying degrees of severity

198
00:08:15,066 --> 00:08:16,600
this is thaumcraft warp

199
00:08:16,866 --> 00:08:19,533
or a way to represent how much dark magic you've dealt into

200
00:08:19,533 --> 00:08:22,966
the more you do the bigger the number and the bigger the consequences

201
00:08:22,966 --> 00:08:25,000
until you're spawning withers in your base

202
00:08:25,833 --> 00:08:28,866
the starting effects range from goofy to quirky to annoying

203
00:08:29,133 --> 00:08:30,866
and the later effects can be downright evil

204
00:08:31,633 --> 00:08:34,300
don't worry about it too much to begin, don't get carried away

205
00:08:35,833 --> 00:08:38,866
the quest book will lead you to how to deal with it in the advanced thaumcraft chapter

206
00:08:38,866 --> 00:08:39,900
but not soon

207
00:08:42,500 --> 00:08:43,566
now about your taint

208
00:08:43,566 --> 00:08:44,800
uh

209
00:08:45,100 --> 00:08:48,866
anyway one of the ways you end up with taint is by introducing too much flux in the world

210
00:08:48,866 --> 00:08:50,033
right, another term

211
00:08:50,433 --> 00:08:51,900
think about flux as excess magic

212
00:08:51,900 --> 00:08:54,100
if you get a bunch of junk and put it in the crucible

213
00:08:54,100 --> 00:08:56,766
and it leaves a bunch of extra junk after making the thing you want

214
00:08:56,766 --> 00:08:57,833
you get flux

215
00:08:58,133 --> 00:09:00,533
you might see this as purple goo that overflows out

216
00:09:00,866 --> 00:09:02,233
a tiny bit is okay

217
00:09:02,300 --> 00:09:04,033
just clean it up by placing blocks on it

218
00:09:04,433 --> 00:09:07,933
too much flux is really, really, really bad

219
00:09:08,433 --> 00:09:11,500
like creating an infinitely spreading tainted lands biome in your base pad

220
00:09:11,866 --> 00:09:14,433
it would take being super careless to end up there

221
00:09:14,433 --> 00:09:16,633
but if you're new to the mod, it's not impossible

222
00:09:17,000 --> 00:09:19,466
there are ways to cheese using the microblocks and trapdoors

223
00:09:19,466 --> 00:09:20,633
but this is a beginner's guide

224
00:09:20,633 --> 00:09:23,800
so we're gonna focus on getting a safe crafting the way the mod provides

225
00:09:24,766 --> 00:09:27,133
quick notes on the thaumonicon and research

226
00:09:27,333 --> 00:09:29,500
the research is split up into pages or chapters

227
00:09:29,500 --> 00:09:30,833
or whatever you want to call them

228
00:09:31,233 --> 00:09:33,366
basic information is where it all begins

229
00:09:33,366 --> 00:09:36,933
and most if not all of these are worth grabbing right away to make the research points go further

230
00:09:36,933 --> 00:09:39,900
and make sure you don't accidentally destroy a node while you're charging your wand

231
00:09:40,133 --> 00:09:41,200
we'll get to that in a sec

232
00:09:41,933 --> 00:09:45,233
thaumaturgy is all about the basics of making and using wands

233
00:09:45,866 --> 00:09:49,400
alchemy is about crafting with the crucible and metal transmutation

234
00:09:50,033 --> 00:09:52,633
artifice is about the tools and utility items

235
00:09:52,866 --> 00:09:55,333
tons of good stuff in there including infusion

236
00:09:56,100 --> 00:09:57,733
and there's lots more chapters

237
00:09:57,933 --> 00:10:00,466
some odd specific ones like blood magic and Botania

238
00:10:00,666 --> 00:10:02,800
and some just containing more cool and useful stuff

239
00:10:03,100 --> 00:10:06,100
some you won't unlock until you go insane, end game

240
00:10:07,133 --> 00:10:09,233
covering everything in this book would take hours

241
00:10:09,233 --> 00:10:10,433
so we aren't doing that here

242
00:10:10,533 --> 00:10:12,866
the main point is you don't need every research

243
00:10:12,866 --> 00:10:14,500
not even every research in a chapter

244
00:10:14,666 --> 00:10:16,333
but trust me you might want them 

245
00:10:16,866 --> 00:10:19,600
everything we're going to cover is in the chapters i just mentioned

246
00:10:19,600 --> 00:10:20,200
so start there

247
00:10:22,000 --> 00:10:23,200
one more thing on research

248
00:10:23,200 --> 00:10:25,033
if you know an item you want ahead of time

249
00:10:25,033 --> 00:10:27,433
say the boots of the traveler for example

250
00:10:27,733 --> 00:10:29,400
you'll see that you don't have the research

251
00:10:29,600 --> 00:10:34,700
one of the tricky parts about thaumcraft is it's hard to know what research unlocks the research you actually want

252
00:10:34,700 --> 00:10:35,433
not in GTNH

253
00:10:36,100 --> 00:10:38,666
hovering over the research name tells you what the parent researches are

254
00:10:38,666 --> 00:10:39,733
and which chapter they're in

255
00:10:39,733 --> 00:10:41,400
which can sometimes be a direct path

256
00:10:41,700 --> 00:10:43,433
if you can't see the prerequisite research either

257
00:10:43,433 --> 00:10:46,433
there's a research cheat sheet in the wiki, linked below

258
00:10:47,033 --> 00:10:48,300
it takes some bouncing around

259
00:10:48,300 --> 00:10:48,900
but in the end

260
00:10:48,900 --> 00:10:50,466
you can find where all the research you need is

261
00:10:50,466 --> 00:10:51,566
and where to unlock it

262
00:10:51,566 --> 00:10:56,133
you can also turn on a mod option to allow you to see the recipes for items you haven't researched yet

263
00:10:56,133 --> 00:10:56,866
mod options

264
00:10:56,866 --> 00:10:58,633
thaumcraft NEI additions

265
00:10:58,633 --> 00:10:59,200
general

266
00:10:59,200 --> 00:11:00,800
show locked recipes

267
00:11:01,433 --> 00:11:02,266
but fair warning

268
00:11:02,500 --> 00:11:05,166
it gets really hard to tell what you've actually researched if it's on

269
00:11:05,166 --> 00:11:06,333
useful though

270
00:11:07,066 --> 00:11:10,800
now going forward i'm gonna assume you simply have all the research you need

271
00:11:10,800 --> 00:11:13,833
if you finish most of what's in the first four chapters of the thaumonicon

272
00:11:13,833 --> 00:11:14,800
you will

273
00:11:16,533 --> 00:11:17,900
to get anywhere with thaumcraft

274
00:11:17,900 --> 00:11:19,166
you need the infusion altar

275
00:11:19,166 --> 00:11:21,300
and to use it, you need jars of essentia

276
00:11:21,300 --> 00:11:24,366
to get those, you need an alchemical furnace and some arcane alembics (?)

277
00:11:24,366 --> 00:11:26,933
and to craft those you need vis in your wand

278
00:11:28,900 --> 00:11:31,066
grab yourself some goggles of revealing

279
00:11:31,066 --> 00:11:31,700
oh wait

280
00:11:32,033 --> 00:11:34,700
your 20 capacity wand is way too garbage for that

281
00:11:34,700 --> 00:11:36,366
we'll fix that momentarily

282
00:11:36,866 --> 00:11:39,233
instead grab your thaumometer and start wandering

283
00:11:39,433 --> 00:11:40,266
you're looking for nodes

284
00:11:40,266 --> 00:11:43,133
which will appear as bright balls of light until you get up close

285
00:11:43,133 --> 00:11:45,833
scan them and you can see which aspects they're made of

286
00:11:45,833 --> 00:11:47,633
they'll mostly be primal aspects

287
00:11:47,633 --> 00:11:49,766
which is good, because that's what you need

288
00:11:49,766 --> 00:11:51,800
searching at night can make them easier to find

289
00:11:51,800 --> 00:11:54,633
they have a slight light signature similar to the beehives

290
00:11:55,433 --> 00:11:59,333
you need at least one of every primal aspect in enough quantity to fill your wand

291
00:11:59,333 --> 00:12:00,466
and the more the better

292
00:12:00,866 --> 00:12:02,666
you shouldn't have to wander too far to get just that

293
00:12:03,566 --> 00:12:05,166
right click with the wand to charge it

294
00:12:05,166 --> 00:12:08,133
and be careful not to drain the nodes empty and destroy them

295
00:12:08,133 --> 00:12:09,300
this wand is bad

296
00:12:12,033 --> 00:12:15,000
your first priority is making a wand good enough to get the goggles of revealing

297
00:12:15,000 --> 00:12:17,566
and ultimately the rest of the vis discount gear you can make early

298
00:12:17,566 --> 00:12:19,400
and stop yourself from breaking nets

299
00:12:20,300 --> 00:12:21,733
since you got lucky with stainless steel

300
00:12:21,733 --> 00:12:23,866
you can jump right to the iron cap greatwood wand

301
00:12:24,266 --> 00:12:25,733
which bumps the vis capacity up to 40

302
00:12:25,733 --> 00:12:27,700
and if you have the node preserver research

303
00:12:27,700 --> 00:12:29,400
will prevent you from breaking nodes

304
00:12:29,433 --> 00:12:31,033
unless you're sneaking while charging

305
00:12:31,933 --> 00:12:33,066
grab the goggles of revealing

306
00:12:33,100 --> 00:12:34,200
find some more nodes

307
00:12:34,200 --> 00:12:35,933
much more easily this time

308
00:12:36,633 --> 00:12:40,033
and get to work on the bewitched robe and bewitched leggings and thaumaturge's boots

309
00:12:40,033 --> 00:12:41,800
to max out your vis discount for crafting

310
00:12:42,133 --> 00:12:44,233
you'll need the spinning wheel and some thaumium

311
00:12:44,600 --> 00:12:46,166
it's time to talk alchemy

312
00:12:47,000 --> 00:12:49,533
the very first thing you want from your crucible is nitor

313
00:12:49,633 --> 00:12:53,400
so craft it up by tossing in four torches, two coal and a piece of glowstone

314
00:12:53,400 --> 00:12:55,200
that was your first perfect craft

315
00:12:55,433 --> 00:12:56,800
goodbye fire

316
00:12:58,266 --> 00:13:02,800
the next thing you want is a large supply of balance shards and thaumium, thaumcraft base metal

317
00:13:02,800 --> 00:13:04,633
toss in four of each shard

318
00:13:04,633 --> 00:13:06,000
finishing with four air shards

319
00:13:06,000 --> 00:13:08,833
and then five iron ingots and five air crystal powder

320
00:13:09,400 --> 00:13:11,233
you should end up with four balance shards

321
00:13:11,233 --> 00:13:13,333
five thaumium and five air shards

322
00:13:13,400 --> 00:13:15,333
with no excess essentia in the crucible

323
00:13:16,066 --> 00:13:17,800
it works the same way with any crystal powder

324
00:13:17,800 --> 00:13:19,600
and with the shards in any order

325
00:13:20,433 --> 00:13:22,633
if you're tired of running all over the place to charge your wand

326
00:13:22,666 --> 00:13:24,333
you'll probably want some primal shrooms

327
00:13:25,066 --> 00:13:27,033
you need to find vishrooms in a magical forest

328
00:13:27,033 --> 00:13:28,366
which hopefully you found long ago

329
00:13:28,366 --> 00:13:30,600
or the biome compass can lead you to easily

330
00:13:30,600 --> 00:13:32,500
get quite literally as many as you can

331
00:13:32,500 --> 00:13:34,100
and buy them from the quest book

332
00:13:35,900 --> 00:13:38,866
a pumpkin and two tiny piles of stone dust and a vishroom

333
00:13:38,866 --> 00:13:39,733
get you a primal

334
00:13:39,933 --> 00:13:41,033
and that's free vis

335
00:13:41,933 --> 00:13:43,466
the watering can works on him as well

336
00:13:43,833 --> 00:13:45,433
no matter how much time you spend doing this

337
00:13:45,433 --> 00:13:47,633
it's less than you would spend roaming node to node

338
00:13:48,200 --> 00:13:49,466
and with thaumium and all the vis you need

339
00:13:49,466 --> 00:13:52,233
you can start using the alchemical furnace with a couple of arcane alembics

340
00:13:52,233 --> 00:13:54,200
to break down items into their component essentias

341
00:13:54,200 --> 00:13:55,600
and store it all in jars

342
00:13:55,600 --> 00:13:57,200
any combustible can fuel it

343
00:13:57,233 --> 00:13:59,233
but aluminum makes it drain essentia faster

344
00:14:00,033 --> 00:14:02,900
you can continue to use a regular crucible setup when you have perfect crafts

345
00:14:02,900 --> 00:14:04,833
like for nitors, balance shards and thaumium

346
00:14:04,833 --> 00:14:08,500
and now aluminum with three coal three tiny piles of stone dust and a coal dust

347
00:14:09,533 --> 00:14:11,066
once there's essentia in the alembic

348
00:14:11,066 --> 00:14:11,833
slap a label on it 

349
00:14:11,833 --> 00:14:13,300
so we'll only accept that type

350
00:14:13,300 --> 00:14:14,266
you can remove them

351
00:14:14,266 --> 00:14:16,600
but this keeps the pipes from making things weird

352
00:14:16,600 --> 00:14:18,700
essentia pipes are super goofy

353
00:14:18,900 --> 00:14:19,800
but for our purposes

354
00:14:19,800 --> 00:14:21,666
just pipe straight into a jar from the alembic

355
00:14:22,500 --> 00:14:23,733
you can label the jars too

356
00:14:23,733 --> 00:14:26,700
and Voila, restoring essentia for future use

357
00:14:26,800 --> 00:14:28,200
and there's no need to wait

358
00:14:29,066 --> 00:14:32,000
if you make a couple of alchemical constructs and stick them on top of crucible

359
00:14:32,100 --> 00:14:34,233
now you got a system for perfect ratio Alchemy

360
00:14:34,466 --> 00:14:36,100
just plug your jars into the sides

361
00:14:36,100 --> 00:14:36,833
and Bingo Bango

362
00:14:37,500 --> 00:14:40,566
you can also and should also upgrade your wand again

363
00:14:40,566 --> 00:14:42,833
this time to the satin entwined greatwood wand

364
00:14:43,400 --> 00:14:45,400
the quest is either or (?) and satin is better

365
00:14:45,400 --> 00:14:46,466
so go for that

366
00:14:47,533 --> 00:14:50,933
slap on your bewitch robes and leggings your goggles and your thaumaturge boots

367
00:14:50,933 --> 00:14:52,800
and get your final wand upgrade for now

368
00:14:53,033 --> 00:14:54,700
the gold banded greatwood scepter

369
00:14:55,200 --> 00:14:58,933
you needed that 50 capacity wand specifically for the primal charm to make the next wand

370
00:14:59,433 --> 00:15:01,633
this is how a wand progression works from here

371
00:15:01,633 --> 00:15:02,466
so get used to it

372
00:15:03,833 --> 00:15:06,533
with this wand you can start bringing home nodes in jars

373
00:15:06,533 --> 00:15:07,633
check the research

374
00:15:07,733 --> 00:15:09,266
shortening your vis recharge even more

375
00:15:09,266 --> 00:15:11,233
and preparing for advanced thaumaturgy

376
00:15:12,000 --> 00:15:13,966
and finally, the infusion altar

377
00:15:14,933 --> 00:15:16,866
this is basically the end of the line for us for now

378
00:15:16,866 --> 00:15:20,433
with this, the rest of thaumcraft and all the other magic mods are open to you

379
00:15:20,600 --> 00:15:23,600
not to mention the best animation in the history of the game

380
00:15:24,333 --> 00:15:26,666
hopefully you found a villager willing to trade you an ender pearl

381
00:15:26,666 --> 00:15:28,500
if not you're waiting until HV for this

382
00:15:28,500 --> 00:15:29,700
which is a big time bummer

383
00:15:29,700 --> 00:15:34,000
because the boots of the traveler are so much better earlier than that

384
00:15:34,000 --> 00:15:35,233
work on those first

385
00:15:35,233 --> 00:15:38,533
and rejoice at how much more convenient getting around is about to become

386
00:15:38,533 --> 00:15:40,466
the recipes show the ingredients around the center

387
00:15:40,466 --> 00:15:41,933
and they don't need to be in perfect order

388
00:15:42,266 --> 00:15:44,333
but they do need to be balanced on the pedestals

389
00:15:44,633 --> 00:15:48,100
if there are four items to the left, put four on the right, and so on

390
00:15:48,100 --> 00:15:50,300
some recipes don't have perfect balance

391
00:15:50,300 --> 00:15:51,833
which can be a little jarring to look at

392
00:15:51,833 --> 00:15:53,033
but they still work

393
00:15:53,033 --> 00:15:55,533
every recipe also has a stability value

394
00:15:56,200 --> 00:15:57,633
once you get the arcane abacus

395
00:15:57,633 --> 00:15:59,333
you can have the recipe laid out on the pedestals

396
00:15:59,333 --> 00:16:01,433
and the abacus will tell you the instability of the recipe

397
00:16:01,433 --> 00:16:02,966
and the stability of your altar

398
00:16:02,966 --> 00:16:05,666
sadly you can't get this until close to the end of MV

399
00:16:05,666 --> 00:16:07,533
when you can get your first hv circuits

400
00:16:07,900 --> 00:16:10,733
before that just overload on stability boosters

401
00:16:11,633 --> 00:16:13,333
there are lots of blocks that can boost stability

402
00:16:13,333 --> 00:16:14,700
and they all tell you that

403
00:16:14,700 --> 00:16:16,700
the easiest way is probably quicksilver blocks

404
00:16:16,800 --> 00:16:18,333
they make a symmetrical pattern under your altar

405
00:16:18,333 --> 00:16:20,533
you can go another couple layers below as well

406
00:16:21,400 --> 00:16:22,733
throw down some skulls or candles

407
00:16:22,733 --> 00:16:25,866
and just make sure the pattern they have is symmetrical for the maximum boost

408
00:16:26,066 --> 00:16:27,366
once you have some stability going

409
00:16:27,366 --> 00:16:28,300
lay out a crafting recipe

410
00:16:28,300 --> 00:16:31,333
and right click the matrix at the center with your wand to start the craft

411
00:16:31,333 --> 00:16:32,633
after the boots of the traveler

412
00:16:32,633 --> 00:16:35,633
it's up to you just how far down the rabbit hole you want to go

413
00:16:36,533 --> 00:16:38,300
so now you know how to get into thaumcraft

414
00:16:38,433 --> 00:16:40,633
the only question left is, why

415
00:16:41,633 --> 00:16:47,000
beyond unlocking the other magic mods and finishing the pack that is well here's the thing

416
00:17:22,133 --> 00:17:24,000
yeah worth

417
00:17:24,533 --> 00:17:26,433
there's also the nano suit boots of the traveler

418
00:17:26,433 --> 00:17:28,633
and the goggles of revealing to go with the rest of your nano suit

419
00:17:28,633 --> 00:17:29,833
which are amazing

420
00:17:30,566 --> 00:17:33,900
and a lot of players, including me, hardline the thaumcraft restorer (?)

421
00:17:34,133 --> 00:17:37,133
which can repair, among other things, the oblivion frames

422
00:17:37,300 --> 00:17:39,300
a crucial early item for bee progression

423
00:17:39,466 --> 00:17:41,900
and the flight potion that grants create a flight

424
00:17:41,900 --> 00:17:43,100
yeah you want this

425
00:17:44,433 --> 00:17:45,700
short bit on bees

426
00:17:45,700 --> 00:17:49,066
they are absurdly good in GTNH for everything

427
00:17:49,100 --> 00:17:50,266
and i mean everything

428
00:17:50,600 --> 00:17:52,600
they're reason enough to get as far as we've gone in the guide

429
00:17:53,100 --> 00:17:54,900
they're the basis of my resource generation

430
00:17:54,900 --> 00:17:56,800
and the power generation in my own world

431
00:17:56,866 --> 00:17:58,333
outrageously good

432
00:17:58,600 --> 00:17:59,933
if you want to learn how to do bees

433
00:17:59,933 --> 00:18:01,333
check out Aditya's guide

434
00:18:01,333 --> 00:18:04,666
by far the most exhaustive and useful guide on GTNH bee that exists

435
00:18:05,200 --> 00:18:07,466
you'll be glad you invested in magic, i'll say that

436
00:18:08,533 --> 00:18:10,700
and if you want to take thaumcraft farther than we've gone here

437
00:18:10,700 --> 00:18:11,833
you'll need better wands

438
00:18:11,833 --> 00:18:15,233
which threefold's GTNH spreadsheet has some amazing information on

439
00:18:15,433 --> 00:18:18,766
as well as information on which items give the clearest source of essentia

440
00:18:18,766 --> 00:18:20,200
routes to both are linked below

441
00:18:21,933 --> 00:18:24,033
so with thaumcraft progression in the bag

442
00:18:24,033 --> 00:18:25,633
you can move on to the other magic mods

443
00:18:25,633 --> 00:18:28,466
all of which have conveniences that are nearly as good or better

444
00:18:29,133 --> 00:18:31,300
how about some herbology next?

445
00:18:31,300 --> 00:18:33,200
Botania has its own research chapter

446
00:18:33,200 --> 00:18:35,266
which i'll assume you've completed as relevant here

447
00:18:36,700 --> 00:18:39,333
it also has its own book, the Lexica Botania

448
00:18:39,433 --> 00:18:41,400
which you should a hundred percent read

449
00:18:41,400 --> 00:18:43,066
great mod book it must be said

450
00:18:43,066 --> 00:18:44,000
cheers vasquez

451
00:18:45,200 --> 00:18:47,600
you can actually get into Botania without doing thaumcraft

452
00:18:47,600 --> 00:18:48,866
but it would be a little painful

453
00:18:49,266 --> 00:18:51,533
no matter what you'll start by wandering the twilight forest

454
00:18:51,533 --> 00:18:53,866
looking for caves that contain shimmering mushrooms

455
00:18:54,133 --> 00:18:55,966
you'll be converting them to flowers using Alchemy

456
00:18:55,966 --> 00:18:57,266
and like with most things

457
00:18:57,266 --> 00:18:59,200
the more you collect the easier it will be to snowball

458
00:18:59,200 --> 00:19:00,333
so keep at it for a bit

459
00:19:00,733 --> 00:19:02,600
but you'll also unlock ways to duplicate them

460
00:19:02,600 --> 00:19:03,600
also through alchemy

461
00:19:03,633 --> 00:19:04,833
or you might have already

462
00:19:05,733 --> 00:19:08,233
the Petal apothecary is the crafting table of Botania

463
00:19:08,433 --> 00:19:11,033
and the first thing you want to make are pure daisies

464
00:19:11,033 --> 00:19:12,400
to use the apothecary

465
00:19:12,433 --> 00:19:13,300
fill with water

466
00:19:13,400 --> 00:19:14,433
drop recipe items in

467
00:19:14,433 --> 00:19:16,933
then toss seeds in to complete the craft

468
00:19:16,933 --> 00:19:19,700
shift right click with an empty hand to repeat the whole recipe

469
00:19:23,233 --> 00:19:24,966
a handful of pure daisies will do it

470
00:19:24,966 --> 00:19:27,400
hop them down and surround each one with logs or stone

471
00:19:27,500 --> 00:19:29,900
and in a jiff, they'll convert to living wood and living rock

472
00:19:32,266 --> 00:19:33,133
with living wood in hand

473
00:19:33,133 --> 00:19:37,233
make your first wand of the forest with a couple of petals and the colors of your preference

474
00:19:37,233 --> 00:19:38,266
now you're ready to rock

475
00:19:38,600 --> 00:19:39,600
living rock

476
00:19:40,300 --> 00:19:42,066
we're Gonna speed run mana generation here

477
00:19:42,066 --> 00:19:42,933
so buckle in

478
00:19:43,533 --> 00:19:44,566
make the diluted mana pool

479
00:19:44,566 --> 00:19:47,433
and get ready to trash it almost immediately

480
00:19:47,433 --> 00:19:50,000
to start, you'll have to use dayblooms and nightshades

481
00:19:50,000 --> 00:19:52,700
one generates mana during the day and the other at night

482
00:19:52,700 --> 00:19:54,900
they die, so make sure you get your money's worth

483
00:19:54,900 --> 00:19:56,233
place a mana spreader nearby

484
00:19:56,233 --> 00:20:00,066
and shift right click on the flower then the spreader while in bind mode to link them

485
00:20:00,500 --> 00:20:02,600
you'll see a green check mark indicating it was successful

486
00:20:02,600 --> 00:20:04,433
and a nice particle effect showing the flow

487
00:20:05,000 --> 00:20:07,100
do the same to the spreader and link it to the mana pool

488
00:20:10,533 --> 00:20:11,800
as soon as you get the visual indicator

489
00:20:11,800 --> 00:20:14,533
that you can make mana steel by dropping a steel ingot into the pool

490
00:20:14,533 --> 00:20:15,333
do it

491
00:20:15,333 --> 00:20:18,200
then immediately replace the diluted pool with a real mana pool

492
00:20:19,500 --> 00:20:22,333
you might even salvage an extra bit of free mana from your first flowers

493
00:20:25,200 --> 00:20:27,333
the next flower you want is the Emdoflame

494
00:20:27,333 --> 00:20:28,733
which can eat combustibles

495
00:20:29,066 --> 00:20:31,900
and whose only real difficulty is the burning blossoms from the nether

496
00:20:32,633 --> 00:20:34,300
with a 30 second timer and a dropper

497
00:20:34,300 --> 00:20:36,700
you can set up an Emdoflame to produce mana for a good long while

498
00:20:36,700 --> 00:20:41,100
you can easily scale the same setup to a bunch of Emdoflames

499
00:20:41,100 --> 00:20:42,833
long term, the thermolilly (?)

500
00:20:42,833 --> 00:20:45,300
paired with an ever burner and cycling buckets into droppers

501
00:20:45,300 --> 00:20:48,533
and otherwise working exactly the same way as the emdoflame setup

502
00:20:48,533 --> 00:20:50,233
using a timer set to five minutes

503
00:20:50,233 --> 00:20:52,566
is going to produce massive amounts of mana

504
00:20:52,566 --> 00:20:55,233
to get that one though you need the runic altar

505
00:20:56,033 --> 00:20:58,000
luckily, you have thaumcraft infusion

506
00:20:58,000 --> 00:20:59,200
so this is no big deal

507
00:20:59,933 --> 00:21:04,300
you get the prismarine shards by dropping nether quartz in a mana pool with the alchemy catalyst underneath the pool

508
00:21:04,300 --> 00:21:05,966
a bit more research and crafting

509
00:21:05,966 --> 00:21:07,100
and they're all yours

510
00:21:07,533 --> 00:21:08,266
once you have it

511
00:21:08,266 --> 00:21:10,066
place a couple of spreaders next to your mana pool

512
00:21:10,066 --> 00:21:11,400
and point them at the altar

513
00:21:13,400 --> 00:21:15,233
right click the recipe items onto the altar

514
00:21:15,233 --> 00:21:17,800
let the mana build up until you get a sweet lightning animation

515
00:21:17,800 --> 00:21:19,133
then toss living rock on the top

516
00:21:19,133 --> 00:21:20,966
and right click with the wand

517
00:21:20,966 --> 00:21:21,433
bazinga

518
00:21:21,733 --> 00:21:22,633
you're runicing

519
00:21:25,300 --> 00:21:26,933
so why Botania

520
00:21:27,733 --> 00:21:28,600
first of all

521
00:21:28,700 --> 00:21:31,666
it looks cool and makes for awesome thematic decoration

522
00:21:32,333 --> 00:21:34,533
secondly though is cheap tiered glass

523
00:21:34,533 --> 00:21:36,600
and an excellent gregtech tool material

524
00:21:37,066 --> 00:21:40,300
mana glass is way easier to make than the equivalent gregtech glass

525
00:21:40,300 --> 00:21:42,400
which you'll need for some of the upcoming multi blocks

526
00:21:42,400 --> 00:21:47,100
and mana steel and after EV terra steel are incredible tool materials for their time

527
00:21:47,866 --> 00:21:49,733
not to mention the Botania tools themselves

528
00:21:49,733 --> 00:21:50,700
which are insane

529
00:21:50,933 --> 00:21:54,300
oh and fantastic potions, resource duplication and transmutation

530
00:21:55,500 --> 00:21:58,066
the single longest crafting recipe in the entire game

531
00:21:58,733 --> 00:22:00,300
and if you get through it all

532
00:22:00,300 --> 00:22:02,700
the most Epic boss battle music of all time

533
00:22:03,833 --> 00:22:04,800
what's not to love

534
00:22:07,133 --> 00:22:09,533
next up, potions with professor Snape

535
00:22:09,733 --> 00:22:11,000
it's time for witchery

536
00:22:11,133 --> 00:22:13,133
and it begins with a bit of farming

537
00:22:13,133 --> 00:22:16,000
actually hoeing the grass away from water to get the witchery seeds

538
00:22:16,300 --> 00:22:17,066
farm them up

539
00:22:17,066 --> 00:22:18,233
and beware the mandrakes

540
00:22:18,900 --> 00:22:20,100
using the crossbow to break the plant

541
00:22:20,100 --> 00:22:22,100
and immediately shoot the little guy tends to work

542
00:22:22,100 --> 00:22:24,533
but if not, just make the earphones

543
00:22:25,166 --> 00:22:27,866
secure the cauldron, the witch's oven and a bunch of clay jars

544
00:22:27,866 --> 00:22:29,800
and start making all the odors and such

545
00:22:29,800 --> 00:22:31,700
thapplings (?) might actually be a problem

546
00:22:31,800 --> 00:22:33,133
you haven't needed them until now

547
00:22:33,200 --> 00:22:34,000
enjoy

548
00:22:35,600 --> 00:22:36,833
light a fire under the cauldron

549
00:22:36,833 --> 00:22:38,100
fill it with three buckets of water

550
00:22:38,100 --> 00:22:40,433
and toss in the items the quest book suggests one at a time

551
00:22:40,433 --> 00:22:41,933
to get yourself some mutandis

552
00:22:45,466 --> 00:22:47,500
and use the mutandis on grass or flowers

553
00:22:47,500 --> 00:22:49,333
until you get three witchery saplings

554
00:22:49,500 --> 00:22:51,533
Rowan, alder and hawthorn

555
00:22:51,933 --> 00:22:53,333
then you might need a bit

556
00:22:54,066 --> 00:22:56,833
farm some wood, and leave a couple of trees grown as well

557
00:22:56,833 --> 00:22:58,933
the next thing you'll need is the witchery altar

558
00:22:59,000 --> 00:23:01,466
and it gets more power the more variety of nature is around it

559
00:23:01,500 --> 00:23:03,500
so max out the different trees and flowers

560
00:23:04,066 --> 00:23:06,533
there are a few other things you can use to upgrade the ultra power as well

561
00:23:06,533 --> 00:23:08,333
toss your own skull on there

562
00:23:08,600 --> 00:23:10,300
candelabra you made with the altar

563
00:23:10,300 --> 00:23:11,833
and the chalice from the quest

564
00:23:12,666 --> 00:23:14,200
if you take the redstone soup award

565
00:23:14,200 --> 00:23:16,333
you can upgrade the chalice right away and make it better

566
00:23:17,633 --> 00:23:20,600
you need 5450 ultra power for the short term goal

567
00:23:20,600 --> 00:23:21,466
and if you're way short

568
00:23:21,466 --> 00:23:23,100
the Dragon egg will take you over the top

569
00:23:23,400 --> 00:23:24,900
though that's a mission of its own

570
00:23:24,900 --> 00:23:26,400
try some more nature first

571
00:23:27,366 --> 00:23:29,200
to follow the quest book to the thing you actually want

572
00:23:29,200 --> 00:23:31,733
you'll need to have a nightmare and visit the spirit world

573
00:23:32,266 --> 00:23:33,500
grab yourself a kettle light

574
00:23:33,500 --> 00:23:34,166
a fire under it

575
00:23:34,166 --> 00:23:35,600
and craft up some brews to sleep

576
00:23:38,600 --> 00:23:41,933
drink a sip of flight potion and night vision potion before you drink the brew

577
00:23:42,066 --> 00:23:43,466
you can't bring anything with you

578
00:23:43,466 --> 00:23:45,966
and you'll want to make this quick, trust me

579
00:23:46,433 --> 00:23:49,500
immediately grab as much to serve cotton as you can find while dodging monsters

580
00:23:49,500 --> 00:23:50,666
and then let one kill you

581
00:23:51,100 --> 00:23:52,800
you're done with this dimension if you want

582
00:23:55,433 --> 00:23:57,333
grab the spinning wheel and the distillery

583
00:23:57,333 --> 00:23:59,133
luckily, your wand is up to snuff for the craft

584
00:23:59,133 --> 00:24:01,433
since you need 80 vis capacity

585
00:24:01,433 --> 00:24:02,800
now you can make the witch's robes

586
00:24:02,800 --> 00:24:04,866
and most importantly diamond vapor

587
00:24:04,933 --> 00:24:07,933
which unlocks the main reason you'd do witchery at all

588
00:24:07,933 --> 00:24:09,633
biome changing potions

589
00:24:09,700 --> 00:24:13,600
absolutely amazing for all those bees that have particular requirements for jubilation (?)

590
00:24:13,900 --> 00:24:15,333
did i mention bees are awesome?

591
00:24:15,933 --> 00:24:16,966
just grab a biome page

592
00:24:16,966 --> 00:24:20,566
and toss the items the quest book suggests into the cauldron to brew

593
00:24:20,566 --> 00:24:22,966
completely worth the effort on its own

594
00:24:22,966 --> 00:24:24,833
to reiterate, these are absurd

595
00:24:25,000 --> 00:24:26,433
but if that's not enough for you

596
00:24:26,833 --> 00:24:28,700
you can get some insane potions from witchery

597
00:24:28,700 --> 00:24:29,800
and the other were infusion

598
00:24:29,800 --> 00:24:31,900
which is a legit substitute for the home command

599
00:24:32,033 --> 00:24:34,500
oh and werewolves you can be a werewolf

600
00:24:34,900 --> 00:24:37,200
there's lots of goofy stuff for multiplayer too

601
00:24:37,300 --> 00:24:41,133
and lastly, you need those attuned stones you've been using to get into blood magic

602
00:24:42,500 --> 00:24:45,466
and so we've arrived at the dark arts with he who must not be named

603
00:24:46,066 --> 00:24:48,133
a joint enrollment class at devastate

604
00:24:48,133 --> 00:24:52,500
fair warning, getting into blood magic is 100 percent going to increase your warp

605
00:24:52,733 --> 00:24:53,766
so if you plan to do it early

606
00:24:53,766 --> 00:24:56,100
plan not to have a way to deal with that

607
00:24:56,100 --> 00:24:58,900
unless you've gone completely nuts with other warpy research

608
00:24:58,900 --> 00:24:59,700
you'll be fine

609
00:25:00,200 --> 00:25:01,700
but your soul is forfeit

610
00:25:01,700 --> 00:25:05,233
the blood altar uses items from thaumcraft and witchery and some others

611
00:25:05,233 --> 00:25:07,100
and requires the implosion compressor

612
00:25:07,133 --> 00:25:10,066
which you can't make until you get HV circuits at the end of MV

613
00:25:10,233 --> 00:25:13,333
and which you otherwise probably wouldn't make until you're thinking about the tier 1 Rocket

614
00:25:13,333 --> 00:25:14,600
but you should for this

615
00:25:14,633 --> 00:25:16,433
and since you only need two double compressed cobble

616
00:25:16,433 --> 00:25:18,066
the powder barrels work fine

617
00:25:18,066 --> 00:25:20,400
the blood altar is a multi block with six tiers

618
00:25:20,400 --> 00:25:22,133
and we'll be rushing the tier 3 altar here

619
00:25:22,833 --> 00:25:25,033
the tier 1 altar is just the block itself

620
00:25:25,200 --> 00:25:26,400
and to fill it with blood at the start

621
00:25:26,400 --> 00:25:28,133
you'll need the dagger of sacrifice

622
00:25:28,800 --> 00:25:30,233
it's time for some bloodletting

623
00:25:30,733 --> 00:25:35,033
this would be a massive literally painful grind if it weren't for your preparation

624
00:25:35,433 --> 00:25:37,733
you've got all the options you need for regeneration potions

625
00:25:37,733 --> 00:25:38,866
and if those don't suit you

626
00:25:38,866 --> 00:25:41,600
a stockpile of red hearts from your blaze farm for instant regen

627
00:25:42,233 --> 00:25:45,533
you might even have some industrious bees giving the regen effect constantly

628
00:25:45,533 --> 00:25:48,733
with nothing, prepare for pure pain

629
00:25:49,433 --> 00:25:52,333
with enough regen, prepare for easy street (?)

630
00:25:52,333 --> 00:25:55,066
craft yourself a ton of blank slates

631
00:25:55,400 --> 00:25:57,400
you can use a hopper or conduit to do 10 at a time

632
00:25:57,400 --> 00:25:59,033
for the cost of a full altar of blood

633
00:25:59,033 --> 00:26:02,500
and a filtered EnderIO conduit for extracting only once you get the rune you want

634
00:26:02,533 --> 00:26:05,300
and nothing else about slate crafting gets better than it is right now

635
00:26:05,300 --> 00:26:08,866
assuming you have dank (?) regen until you get a ton of upgrade runes

636
00:26:09,000 --> 00:26:12,100
which you can't make until you have a tier 3 altar and a ton of slates

637
00:26:12,533 --> 00:26:14,866
A TON OF SLATES

638
00:26:17,200 --> 00:26:19,066
and of course, the tier 1 blood orb

639
00:26:19,200 --> 00:26:19,833
once you have it

640
00:26:19,833 --> 00:26:21,433
right click while holding it to bind it

641
00:26:21,433 --> 00:26:23,900
then stick it back in the altar and let it soak up some blood

642
00:26:24,433 --> 00:26:25,800
you now have an LP network

643
00:26:27,400 --> 00:26:29,700
the divination sigil will tell you how much LP you have

644
00:26:29,700 --> 00:26:31,533
and there are a bunch of other cool sigils too

645
00:26:32,233 --> 00:26:34,966
it takes eight blank runes to upgrade the altar to tier 2

646
00:26:34,966 --> 00:26:37,133
and snag your tier 2 orb while you're there

647
00:26:37,133 --> 00:26:38,900
and another 20 to upgrade to tier 3

648
00:26:39,433 --> 00:26:42,600
four blank slates per rune for a total of 112 slates

649
00:26:42,600 --> 00:26:45,266
and that's before you can get any runes that improve blood generation

650
00:26:45,933 --> 00:26:48,000
each tier of the altar adds a tier of slate

651
00:26:48,000 --> 00:26:49,266
and you'll want a bunch of tier 2

652
00:26:49,266 --> 00:26:50,633
and at least a handful of tier 3

653
00:26:50,633 --> 00:26:52,833
besides the ones you need for the rune upgrades

654
00:26:52,933 --> 00:26:54,800
yeah you're gonna need a lot of blood

655
00:26:55,300 --> 00:26:58,300
the tier 3 altar also requires blood soak thaumium blocks

656
00:26:58,300 --> 00:26:59,666
so i hope you stocked up earlier

657
00:27:00,133 --> 00:27:03,866
and the tier 3 blood orb specifically requires 30 thousand blood

658
00:27:04,100 --> 00:27:05,766
so using speed runes might hurt you

659
00:27:05,766 --> 00:27:08,166
unless you grind out some augment and capacity runes too

660
00:27:08,866 --> 00:27:12,933
no matter what, you need to invest in runes before you'll be successful in making the tier 3 orb

661
00:27:13,100 --> 00:27:14,633
but you need titanium for that anyway

662
00:27:14,633 --> 00:27:15,866
so you aren't making it now

663
00:27:15,933 --> 00:27:18,700
and that means you have time to make the upgrade runes before the end of HV

664
00:27:19,133 --> 00:27:21,800
which means you also have time for a little bit of blood Alchemy

665
00:27:22,600 --> 00:27:23,700
after a bit more research

666
00:27:23,700 --> 00:27:25,333
you can make the alchemist chemistry set

667
00:27:25,633 --> 00:27:28,133
this thing has quite a few very useful recipes

668
00:27:28,133 --> 00:27:30,300
but for now, you're after alchemy ingredients

669
00:27:31,066 --> 00:27:32,233
simple catalyst

670
00:27:32,466 --> 00:27:33,666
strengthen catalyst

671
00:27:33,866 --> 00:27:34,933
Sanctus

672
00:27:34,933 --> 00:27:35,933
Tenebrae

673
00:27:35,933 --> 00:27:37,466
Incendium

674
00:27:38,000 --> 00:27:38,900
Potentia

675
00:27:39,466 --> 00:27:40,133
Aether

676
00:27:41,066 --> 00:27:41,633
Terrae

677
00:27:42,200 --> 00:27:43,366
and Aquasalus

678
00:27:44,633 --> 00:27:45,400
there are a few more too

679
00:27:45,400 --> 00:27:46,300
but with all these

680
00:27:46,300 --> 00:27:48,900
you'll be free to make that big decision

681
00:27:48,900 --> 00:27:51,000
self sacrifice or sacrifice

682
00:27:51,600 --> 00:27:53,900
you're going to sit tight at this level of blood magic for a bit

683
00:27:54,066 --> 00:27:55,933
so some self sacrifice runes are worth it

684
00:27:56,233 --> 00:27:58,100
they'll speed up the finger pricking substantially

685
00:27:58,866 --> 00:28:01,233
consider the glass dagger of sacrifice if you go this route

686
00:28:02,066 --> 00:28:03,633
if you plan to use the well of suffering

687
00:28:03,633 --> 00:28:05,300
which you will eventually no matter what

688
00:28:05,300 --> 00:28:07,466
you're gonna want runes of sacrifice instead

689
00:28:08,033 --> 00:28:10,400
the problem is you need a tier 4 altar for that

690
00:28:10,466 --> 00:28:13,766
and that will require more thaumcraft progression than you've done

691
00:28:13,766 --> 00:28:14,300
a lot more

692
00:28:14,466 --> 00:28:16,066
the dangerous kind

693
00:28:16,766 --> 00:28:19,800
from this point, the quest book does a decent job of walking you through things

694
00:28:19,800 --> 00:28:21,433
they also start to overlap a bit

695
00:28:21,433 --> 00:28:23,033
and get a little bit complicated

696
00:28:23,033 --> 00:28:25,866
so we may circle back for another round of magic at some point later in the guide

697
00:28:25,866 --> 00:28:27,766
let me know if that interests you

698
00:28:27,766 --> 00:28:28,700
maddening frames

699
00:28:28,700 --> 00:28:31,100
which you might be able to make now if you've already gotten into bees a bit

700
00:28:31,100 --> 00:28:32,866
and is incredible for bee breeding

701
00:28:33,566 --> 00:28:34,866
the well of suffering

702
00:28:34,866 --> 00:28:36,700
for infinite blood generation

703
00:28:39,133 --> 00:28:40,033
bound tools

704
00:28:40,033 --> 00:28:44,933
unbreakable tools that obliterate entire veins in one swing

705
00:28:44,933 --> 00:28:45,866
bound armor

706
00:28:45,866 --> 00:28:47,700
that makes you nearly invincible

707
00:28:47,700 --> 00:28:49,100
and looks sick

708
00:28:49,100 --> 00:28:50,666
energy blasters

709
00:28:50,666 --> 00:28:53,666
for firing off devastating energy attacks

710
00:28:55,233 --> 00:28:56,866
and if you're able to put it all together

711
00:28:56,866 --> 00:28:59,733
completely automated resource from blood magic meteors

712
00:29:00,066 --> 00:29:02,600
interdimensional item transport using magic mirrors

713
00:29:03,000 --> 00:29:06,466
and enough item intake to deal with everything you've got

714
00:29:07,100 --> 00:29:08,300
and thaumic energetics

715
00:29:08,500 --> 00:29:10,933
digital essentia storage and automation

716
00:29:11,600 --> 00:29:12,700
magic is insane

717
00:29:12,700 --> 00:29:14,866
and insanely underappreciated

718
00:29:15,433 --> 00:29:17,433
GTNH is obviously a tech pack

719
00:29:17,633 --> 00:29:19,233
there's a lot more than that under the hood

720
00:29:19,866 --> 00:29:21,933
you got plenty to explore as you make more aluminum

721
00:29:21,933 --> 00:29:23,066
repair your power system

722
00:29:23,066 --> 00:29:25,633
and get yourself ready for the beast that is in MV

723
00:29:26,266 --> 00:29:27,500
see you there for episode 7

724
00:00:00,300 --> 00:00:02,533
你就是无法抗拒，是吗？

725
00:00:03,000 --> 00:00:05,466
魔法的诱惑太强烈了

726
00:00:06,033 --> 00:00:08,633
掌握Gregtech的力量对你来说还不够

727
00:00:09,200 --> 00:00:11,866
只有绝对的力量才足够

728
00:00:11,866 --> 00:00:13,233
神奇输液

729
00:00:13,500 --> 00:00:15,300
血腥牺牲

730
00:00:15,800 --> 00:00:17,266
巫术酿造品

731
00:00:17,933 --> 00:00:20,533
你想要这一切，你需要这一切

732
00:00:21,333 --> 00:00:22,533
但是它从哪里开始呢？

733
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:25,433
当然就在这里

734
00:00:25,500 --> 00:00:26,666
恭喜

735
00:00:26,833 --> 00:00:29,600
你等了一辈子的霍格沃茨的信刚刚到了

736
00:00:29,933 --> 00:00:32,866
欢迎来到gregtech新视野初学者指南

737
00:00:33,066 --> 00:00:36,133
第六集魔术

738
00:00:49,866 --> 00:00:51,166
我们到了新基地

739
00:00:51,166 --> 00:00:52,433
认识设计吗？

740
00:00:53,200 --> 00:00:56,966
今天我们涵盖Thaumcraft、Botania、巫术和血魔法的基础知识

741
00:00:57,533 --> 00:01:01,333
足以让你继续前进，走向魔法能在GTNH为你提供的许多快乐

742
00:01:02,066 --> 00:01:04,000
哦，对了，这是GTNH。

743
00:01:04,500 --> 00:01:08,566
这意味着魔法比你见过的任何东西都更有用更能整合

744
00:01:08,566 --> 00:01:10,833
也比平时复杂一点

745
00:01:12,466 --> 00:01:14,333
一如既往要事第一

746
00:01:14,700 --> 00:01:17,400
请记住，至少目前这一切都是可选的

747
00:01:17,400 --> 00:01:18,733
但有巨大的好处

748
00:01:19,433 --> 00:01:21,266
和其他东西一样，你越早得到它们

749
00:01:21,266 --> 00:01:22,466
他们得到的回报就越多

750
00:01:22,900 --> 00:01:25,933
现在对魔法太着迷还为时过早

751
00:01:26,033 --> 00:01:27,300
但现在你有铝了

752
00:01:27,466 --> 00:01:31,033
还有一段时间等待得到足够的东西来制造你在上一集之后计划的电力系统

753
00:01:31,033 --> 00:01:31,933
你可以开始了

754
00:01:32,300 --> 00:01:33,800
如果你在战利品方面有点幸运

755
00:01:33,833 --> 00:01:35,000
你可以走得很远

756
00:01:35,266 --> 00:01:37,966
长短是你需要不锈钢

757
00:01:37,966 --> 00:01:40,600
总共16块带你了解你将在这里看到的一切

758
00:01:40,600 --> 00:01:41,700
和几只眼睛的安德

759
00:01:41,700 --> 00:01:44,933
在你有机器可以用hv制造它们之前，你可以从村民那里得到它们。

760
00:01:45,433 --> 00:01:46,700
即使你确实幸运地得到了战利品

761
00:01:46,700 --> 00:01:48,800
本指南将带你直到MV结束才能完成

762
00:01:48,800 --> 00:01:50,233
你需要一些MV机器

763
00:01:50,233 --> 00:01:51,133
所以记住这一点

764
